Gentoo base template configuration.

Gentoo is a rolling-release source distribution, so the template is NOT
versioned like Debian/Fedora. The template name is simply the flavor, e.g.
gentoo-xfce, gentoo, gentoo-minimal.

Flavor is configurable via pillar:
  qvm:gentoo:flavor (default: xfce)

IMPORTANT: Qubes OS does not ship a ready-to-clone Gentoo template in the
default repositories (as of 2026 the prebuilt gentoo-minimal was removed from
the Template Manager). The Gentoo template must be built from source with
qubes-builder (qubes-template-configs) or installed from a community repo when
available. See salt/gentoo/README.md. This formula only clones/derives from an
already-installed Gentoo template; it does not build the base template itself.
#}

{% from 'config.jinja' import cfg with context -%}
{% set base = 'gentoo' -%}
{% set flavor = cfg.qvm.get('gentoo', {}).get('flavor', 'xfce') -%}
{% if flavor -%}
  {% set flavor = '-' ~ flavor -%}
{% endif -%}
{% set template = base ~ flavor -%}
{% set template_clean = base ~ flavor -%}
